<h2>1. Our Commitment</h2>
<p>At Patify, ensuring the online safety of children is among our top priorities. We maintain a zero-tolerance policy towards any content or behavior involving child sexual abuse and exploitation (CSAE).</p>

<h2>2. What is CSAE?</h2>
<p>CSAE refers to content or conduct that sexually exploits or abuses children. This includes, but is not limited to:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Grooming a child for sexual exploitation</li>
    <li>Sextortion</li>
    <li>Trafficking a child for sexual purposes</li>
    <li>Any similar actions</li>
</ul>

<h2>3. Prevention and Response</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Content Monitoring:</strong> All content shared within our application is regularly monitored to detect any CSAE-related material.</li>
    <li><strong>User Reporting:</strong> Users have access to a reporting mechanism to flag suspicious content or behavior.</li>
    <li><strong>Prompt Action:</strong> Reported content is promptly reviewed, and, when necessary, reported to the appropriate legal authorities.</li>
</ul>

